--package com.example.myfirstapp

Running Your Application (saved MyFirstApp1/)
========================
ant debug
---------
[dx] UNEXPECTED TOP-LEVEL EXCEPTION:

build-tools: downgrade to 18.1.1 (from 19)

WITHOUT in "AndroidManifest.xml"
	<uses-sdk android:minSdkVersion="8" android:targetSdkVersion="17" />

With "<uses-sdk...>", try "build-tools 19"(???)
	<uses-sdk android:minSdkVersion="8" android:targetSdkVersion="17" />
This means .apk could be installed on the target system whose API level >= 8.


Building a Simple User Interface (saved MyFirstApp2)
================================
activity_main.xml -> main.xml
not RelativeLayout, already LinearLayout

To update(reinstall) .apk, first uninstall like
	adb uninstall com.example.myfirstapp


Starting Another Activity (saved MyFirstApp3)
=========================
1. No resource identifier found for attribute 'parentActivityName' in package 'android'
	>= Android 4.1 (API level 16)

In a test,
to use a smaller system-image and to access local web page (10.0.2.2),
I am using Android 2.3.3 (API level: 10).
Comment these:
        android:parentActivityName="com.example.myfirstapp.MainActivity" >
        <meta-data
            android:name="android.support.PARENT_ACTIVITY"
            android:value="com.example.myfirstapp.MainActivity" />

Moreove, do not use "onOptionsItemSelected". So, no "ActionBar" is available.

2. In a new DisplayMessageActivity.java, be sure to set an appropriate import:
	package com.example.myfirstapp;

	import android.app.Activity;
	import android.os.Bundle;
	import android.view.MenuItem;
	import android.widget.TextView;
	import android.content.Intent;
Also do not use "onCreate" in "Create the Second Activity" section,
instead, use one in "Display the Message" section.


How about using Andoid 2.3.3 above?
===================================
<uses-sdk android:minSdkVersion="8" android:targetSdkVersion="17" />
